{"id":"1915","paper":{"title":{"text":"Local recovery properties of capacity-achieving codes"},"authors":[{"name":"Mazumdar, Arya"},{"name":"Wornell, Gregory"},{"name":"Chandar, Venkat"}],"abstr":{"text":"A code is called locally recoverable or repairable if any symbol of a codeword can be recovered by reading only a small (constant) number of other symbols. The notion of local recoverability is important in the area of distributed storage where a most frequent error-event is a single storage node failure.  A common objective is to repair the node by downloading data from as few other storage node as possible. In this paper we study the basic error-correcting properties of a locally recoverable code. We provide tight upper and lower bound on the local recoverability of a code that achieves capacity of a symmetric channel. In particular it is shown that, if the code-rate is u less than the capacity then for the optimal codes, the local recoverability must scale as log (1/u)."},"body":{"text":""},"refs":[]},"file":{"jsonClass":"File","file":"/home/arnfred/Code/trailhead/resources/ita2013/1915"},"links":[{"id":"205","weight":10},{"id":"2760","weight":45},{"id":"1486","weight":2},{"id":"2741","weight":2},{"id":"3180","weight":3},{"id":"67","weight":17},{"id":"2206","weight":2},{"id":"1606","weight":5},{"id":"3037","weight":15},{"id":"93","weight":6},{"id":"436","weight":4},{"id":"3191","weight":7},{"id":"12","weight":3},{"id":"223","weight":2},{"id":"1547","weight":3},{"id":"2254","weight":7},{"id":"1278","weight":5},{"id":"2287","weight":4},{"id":"3200","weight":16},{"id":"3008","weight":6},{"id":"3083","weight":3},{"id":"2217","weight":8},{"id":"3222","weight":4},{"id":"2291","weight":8},{"id":"307","weight":3},{"id":"1430","weight":4},{"id":"3021","weight":17},{"id":"3199","weight":2},{"id":"813","weight":2},{"id":"3069","weight":5},{"id":"2634","weight":4},{"id":"526","weight":2},{"id":"2442","weight":11},{"id":"3183","weight":12},{"id":"175","weight":4},{"id":"2763